    "Nevertheless, owing to their enormous reliance on historical bug-fixing data, researchers nowadays tend to explore more lightweight approaches using LLMs without re-training/fine-tuning [54][55][56].",
    "Different from the above approaches, given the autogenerated test cases for evaluation, our idea can employ the specific error information fetched from the program execution results to assist the program repair during the Translation Repair Phase.",
    "This section introduces the motivation of Unitrans, which is derived from an in-depth analysis of failed cases of LLMs.",
    "In fact, we first conducted an empirical study on four translation datasets, i.e., C++ to Java, Java to C++, C++ to Python, and Python to C++, with two evaluation metrics, i.e.,Exploring and Unleashing the Power of Large Language Models in Automated Code Translation 71:5Computational Accuracy (CA) and Exact Match Accuracy (EM Acc) mentioned in Section 5.3, to explore the performance of various recent LLMs against state-of-the-art learning-based transpilers.",
    "The detailed experimental setting, dataset, and results are presented in Section 5 and 6.1."
